kea beak
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the token beak from a slaughtered kea, used to collect money from Council, in the attempt to reduce numbers of high-country killer keas.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
