Source:  Grey River Argus
Author:
Vol / Page:  4
Edition:
Quote:  Would the Council urge the [Tourist] Department to take adequate measures for the destruction of keas on their reserves, otherwise their recent increased 'kea beak' subsidy will be partly nullified; or, failing that, would they advise me if one has the right to proceed on to the Government ground in order to destroy birds gazetted as noxious. it was said that the tourist guides made money out of the birds by selling them to tourists at 10s each.
